<TEXT>
the cuban government has checked 27 million 
people more than a quarter of the islands population for aids 
and found 248 infected with the virus the cuban news agency prensa 
latina reports 
ten people have died of the disease and 28 are ill the agency 
said it was not clear if the dead and sick were included among the 
248 found to be infected 
people who test positively for aids antibodies are tested 
further and confined in a health center prensa latina said in the 
report wednesday it said attempts are made to locate others they 
may have infected with the disease which has no known cure 
people who test positive for aids antibodies do not necessarily 
have the disease but may later develop it 
the agency said blood given by blood donors was tested for the 
virus but the dispatch monitored in mexico did not say how 
others were chosen for testing 
cuban authorities the government news agency said are carrying 
out an extensive education campaign in an effort to stop the spread 
of aids on the island of 10 million 
the disease is spread primarily through sexual contact and 
sharing of needles by drug users 
</TEXT>
