here is a chronology of the two weeks of 
labor unrest leading up to solidarity leader lech walesas first 
meeting with top government officials since 1982 
aug 16 angry miners declare occupation strike at manifest 
lipcowy mine in jasztrebie after they were disappointed by 
paychecks 
aug 17 miners at morcinek mine near jastrzebie and port 
workers in szczecin declare solidarity strikes with manifest 
lipcowy 
aug 18 five mines in southwestern poland and port and dock 
workers in szczecin are now on strike 
aug 19 the governments council of ministers issues 
communique saying it will not recognize banned solidarity union 
federation chief demand of the strikers 
aug 21 twelve mines and port and dock workers in szczecin on 
strike lenin shipyard in gdansk announces strike for monday aug 
22 
aug 22 strike begins at lenin shipyard in gdansk police 
storm striking bus depot in gdansk 
aug 25 police clear strikers from three mines 
aug 26 polands roman catholic bishops issue appeal for 
peaceful end to strikes interior minister gen czeslaw kiszczak 
proposes roundtable talks with representatives of workers 
aug 27 plenum of communist party central committee opens in 
warsaw 
sunday plenum endorses roundtable idea 
monday strikes intensify at stalowa wola steel mill in 
southern poland 
tuesday walesa announces he will travel to warsaw for first 
meeting with polish authorities in six years 
wednesday walesa meets with kiszczak on eighth anniversary of 
signing of gdansk agreements that legalized solidarity and calls 
for polish workers to return to work 
</TEXT>
