<TEXT>
the us warship vincennes begins its 
13000 journey home sunday ending a persian gulf assignment marred 
by tragedy 
the departure will represent the first cutback in american 
forces in the gulf since the iraniraq ceasefire 
the 9600ton missile cruiser officially will be detached sunday 
from the navys joint task force middle east navy sources said 
allowing for a months sailing time and at least one port call en 
route the vincennes should reach san diego in midoctober 
the departure ends the vincennes first combat zone assignment 
since being christened at a mississippi shipyard in 1984 by marilyn 
quayle wife of indiana sen dan quayle the republican nominee for 
vice president 
on july 3 the vincennes crew shot down an iranian civilian 
jetliner over the strait of hormuz killing all 290 aboard after 
mistaking the a300 airbus for an attacking f14 fighter 
pentagon officials attributed the blunder to crew stress in 
combat but ruled out punitive action and said iran shared the blame 
by allowing the jetliner to fly over a skirmish between the 
vincennes and iranian gunboats 
while in the gulf region the vincennes also rescued five 
iranian fishermen adrift for eight days after their boat sank 
its withdrawal from the carrier battle group in the arabian sea 
trims the american naval force in the region from 27 to 26 warships 
the pentagon says the us fleet will be scaled back further if 
the ceasefire between iran and iraq which took effect aug 20 
holds 
but it has given no timetable and other ships in the force are 
still being replaced on schedule 
us officials said withdrawing the vincennes was a gesture 
toward reducing tensions 
the vincennes entered the gulf may 27 the first of the navys 
billiondollar aegis cruisers assigned to the waterway 
some critics questioned the deployment of a floating powerhouse 
designed for longrange fleet defense to the tight congested 
gulf even some of the ships officers admitted they were less than 
clear about their assignment 
senior us officials said the vincennes would greatly expand 
air surveillance capability and offset an iranian missile threat 
shortly after arriving the cruiser was out of action for radar 
system repairs us officials said the problem was unrelated to 
the airbus incident 
the vincennes later idled at anchor in manama for another two 
weeks while a us team investigated the jetliner downing it then 
was reassigned to the navys carrier group in the arabian sea and 
did not return to the gulf 
it also made a port visit to the seychelles islands off the 
african coast the 385member crews first real liberty since the 
airbus tragedy 
