<TEXT>
iran brainwashed iraqi prisoners of war 
turning many into fanatical supporters of iran and many pows from 
both nations are afraid to return home a un report said thursday 
the prisoners fear interrogation about their loyalty to their 
homeland becaue they surrendered said the report by three un 
experts who visited iranian and iraqi pow camps in late july and 
early august 
similar problems accompanied negotiations for the voluntary 
return of prisoners that prolonged the korean war for more than a 
year until april 1953 
iran and iraq now under a unbrokered ceasefire in their 
eightyear war are deadlocked in peace talks in geneva over the 
withdrawal of forces and rights to the shattalarab waterway 
forming their border the talks also are supposed to arrange the 
prompt repatriation of prisoners 
the un experts are maj gen rene bats of the belgian army and 
