when the ganges river swollen with floodwaters coursing down from 
the himalayan foothills in neighboring india inundated this 
village of 500 people about 70 miles west of dhaka 
since the rainy season started in june more than 680 people 
have died in bangladesh the new nation and other dhaka newspapers 
said thursday the government whose toll is generally considered 
to be understated puts the toll at 250 
the government estimates the floods have displaced 25 million 
people nearly onefourth of bangladeshs population 
