permits already had been granted should bring the total to 200000 
to 225000 barrels a day 
current california production is about 100000 barrels a day 
nearly twice the 53700 barrels a day in 1981 and almost quadruple 
the 27900 barrels a day in 1980 
federal waters currently hold 16 producing platforms and 22 
should be in operation in 1992 after additions and retirements 
officials said 
almost all production is from the santa barbara channel and the 
santa maria basin 
