sam arvin gathered thousands of pull 
tabs from aluminum cans to help people suffering from kidney 
failure only to learn what other wouldbe dogooders have learned 
before that the tabs are worthless 
the 53yearold janitor broke the tabs from countless aluminum 
cans and persuaded about 100 colleagues at the auto plant where he 
works to do the same he even went to texas to get the tabs from 
4000 aluminum cans in a nephews collection 
he believed the tabs could be cashed in for time on a dialysis 
machine for patients with kidney failure but when he tried to 
redeem them officials of bethany medical center and the national 
kidney foundation told that no such program existed 
i really wanted to help these unfortunate people he said 
i wanted to take pictures of the patients and publish them in our 
company newspaper to get more people interested 
