vincenio tovar said the ruling party had packed the gallery he 
said spectators included a large military contingent 
when the ruling party doesnt have the backing of the peopl 
they have to bring their own supporters he said 
after the walkout de la madrid departed from his text to call 
for tolerance even in the face of insults by our political 
adversaries 
a presidential aide who spoke on condition of anonymity said the 
protests might be new but were normal in any parliamentary 
system and manuel camacho solis general secretary of the pri 
praised what he viewed as de la madrids coolness under fire 
we condemn the intentions and tyrannies of the small group 
