majority camacho solis said in a statement 
there were also interruptions as de la madrid spoke of his 
economic policy which reduced government control of the economy 
encouraged domestic and foreign investment and sharply reduced 
inflation 
but mexicans paid the price with a drastic reduction in buying 
power and lifestyle as petroleum prices and the mexican currency 
collapsed 
the austerity was needed de la madrid said becase we had to 
face and accept the fact that we would have to live within our 
means 
the crisis we have lived through shook the very foundations of 
our social structure de la madrid said it is was though we 
had run the rapids in the current of history it was rough but we 
also made considerable progress 
the new congress was the result of the political reforms 
sponsored by de la madrid and he lashed out at opposition parties 
that have criticized the electoral process and accused his 
administration of abetting electoral fraud 
political pluralism is a vital sign of democracy he said 
and should never be a symptom of a divided or splintered nation 
negotiations between the pri and the opposition had made it 
possible only two days ago to install the new congress in time for 
the de la madrids sixth and final state of the nation message the 
pri holds 260 seats in the chamber of deputies to 139 for the 
leftist democratic front and 101 for the rightist national action 
party 
the pris stranglehold on power has been so strong that until 
this year no opposition candidate had ever been elected to the 
senate now four of 64 senators belong to the leftist opposition 
the same fractious congress must in the next two months 
certify the election of de la madrids chosen successor carlos 
salinas de gortari 
salinas the pri candidate won barely more than 50 percent of 
the popular vote cuauhtemoc cardenas the democratic front 
candidate took 31 percent in the official count but claims he was 
the actual winner 
on other matters de la madrid said mexico will continue its 
fight against drug trafficking and in a clear reference to the 
united states added we hope that everyone is doing their 
part mexico he said cannot fight drugs successfully unless 
the demand for drugs is combated in major centers of consumption 
de la madrid said the problem of mexicos foreign debt now at 
104 billion has not been resolved despite renegotiation and 
the sale of mexican government bonds 
in a preview of what is expected to be salinas policy de la 
madrid said mexico must insist on greater joint responsibility 
and understanding on the part of the creditors in order to achieve 
a solution to the problem they helped to foster 
