government report scheduled for friday on august unemployment 
the labor departments monthly jobless reports are considered 
sensitive signals of the us economys health low unemployment 
implies faster growth higher inflation and rising interest rates 
conversely higher unemployment implies a slowing economy lower 
inflation and eased interest rates 
if the labor departments report shows an unexpected drop in 
joblessness the dollar could rally sharply some moneymarket 
